REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------
1)	You need to run an Apache server and a MySQL server on your machine.
	You can obtain a copy at
		Windows:	http://www.apachefriends.org/de/xampp-windows.html
		Max:		http://www.apachefriends.org/de/xampp-macosx.html
		Linux:		http://www.apachefriends.org/de/xampp-linux.html
		
2)	The software was tested with the following browsers:
	- Chrome 10+
	- Chromium 12+
	- Firefox 8+
	- Opera 11+
	- Internet Explorer 9+
	- Safari 5+
	- Konqueror 4.7+
	If you experience any problems try updating your browser or use one of the browsers listed above.
	As this software uses the HTML canvas element it is likely that this software will not run on older browser (especially IE prior to version 9).




INSTALLATION
-----------------------------------
1)	Extract all files of the ZIP / tar.gz / tar.bz2 file and copy the folder "ProcessManagement" to the root of your webserver (like /htdocs/).

2)	Access the file "Processmanagement/db/include/db.config.php" and enter the correct data for your database server.

3)	Start your Apache server and the MySQL server.

4)	You can now access the site via http://localhost/ProcessManagement.
	The software will automatically create the database and the tables needed.

NOTE: Currently it is not possible to prefix the database tables. To avoid trouble please use a separate database for this software.  
